```@raw html
using NewsvendorModel, Distributions,  StatsBase, Plots</code></pre>



<div class="markdown"><h1>Nahmias &amp; Olson: Production and Operations Analysis</h1>
<p>This notebook illustrates the usage of <a href="https://github.com/frankhuettner/NewsvendorModel.jl">NewsvendorModel.jl</a> with examples from the excellent textbook by <strong>Nahmias &amp; Olson 7th</strong> or <a href="https://www.waveland.com/browse.php?t&#61;662">8th</a> edition.</p>
<p>These notes are not self-contained but should be considered as a companion to the above text book.</p>
<h2>Example Mac</h2>
<p>Unit values:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>cost per unit ordered &#61; 75</p>
</li>
<li><p>selling price per unit &#61; 25</p>
</li>
<li><p>salvage value &#61; 10</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>The following is known about the demand distribution &#40;empirical from previous data&#41;</p>
</div>


<div class="markdown"><h3>Demand and distribution fitting</h3>
</div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'># store the given data in the variable `observed_demand`
observed_demand = vec([15 19 9 12 9 22 4 7 8 11 14 11 6 11 9 18 10 0 14 12 8 9 5 4 4 17 18 14 15 8 6 7 12 15 15 19 9 10 9 16 8 11 11 18 15 17 19 14 14 17 13 12])</code></pre>
<pre id='var-observed_demand' class='code-output documenter-example-output'>52-element Vector{Int64}:
 15
 19
  9
 12
  9
 22
  4
  ⋮
 19
 14
 14
 17
 13
 12</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>D̄ = mean(observed_demand)</code></pre>
<pre id='var-D̄' class='code-output documenter-example-output'>11.73076923076923</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>s = std(observed_demand)</code></pre>
<pre id='var-s' class='code-output documenter-example-output'>4.740792457192357</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>begin
    h1 = fit(Histogram,observed_demand, nbins=10)

    plot(h1, ylabel="Observed frequency", xlabel = "Number of sales", legend=nothing)
    
    d = Normal(D̄, s)
    lo, hi = quantile.(d, [0.01, 0.99])
    x = range(lo, hi; length = 100)
    plot(twinx(), x, pdf.(d, x), legend=nothing, color = :red, yticks = false)
end</code></pre>
<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,">


<div class="markdown"><p>An alternative is to use MLE:</p>
</div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>fit(Normal, observed_demand)</code></pre>
<pre id='var-hash135532' class='code-output documenter-example-output'>Normal{Float64}(μ=11.73076923076923, σ=4.694986624931324)</pre>


<div class="markdown"><h3>Newsvendor Model</h3>
</div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'># Define the model
mac = NVModel(cost = 25, price = 75, salvage = 10, demand = Normal(D̄, s)  )</code></pre>
<pre id='var-mac' class='code-output documenter-example-output'>Data of the Newsvendor Model
 * Demand distribution: Normal{Float64}(μ=11.73076923076923, σ=4.740792457192357)
 * Unit cost: 25.00
 * Unit selling price: 75.00
 * Unit salvage value: 10.00
</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'># Solve the model
solve(mac)</code></pre>
<pre id='var-hash131998' class='code-output documenter-example-output'>=====================================
Results of maximizing expected profit

 * Expected profit: 492.69
=====================================

 * Expected sales: 11.04 units

 * Expected salvage revenue: 39.59
-------------------------------------
</pre>
```

## Some exercises
```@raw html
<div class="markdown">

<p>The book offers exercises with solutions. Here is a small selection that illustrates the convinience of Distributions.jl and NewsvendorModel.jl &#40;everything is very brief and a detailed explanation can be found in the book&#41;.</p>
<h3>Mac&#39;s thesaurus</h3>
</div>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>c = 0.75; b = .5 - (2.75 - c)</code></pre>
<pre id='var-b' class='code-output documenter-example-output'>-1.5</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>thesaurus_nvm = NVModel(cost = c, 
                        price = 2.75, 
                        # demand = Normal(180, 60),
                        demand = truncated(Normal(180, 60), 0, Inf),
                        backorder = b, 
                        salvage = c - c * 0.2 / 12
)</code></pre>
<pre id='var-thesaurus_nvm' class='code-output documenter-example-output'>Data of the Newsvendor Model
 * Demand distribution: Truncated(Normal{Float64}(μ=180.0, σ=60.0); lower=0.0)
 * Unit cost: 0.75
 * Unit selling price: 2.75
 * Unit salvage value: 0.74
 * Unit backorder penalty: -1.50
</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>myp = (
 (2.75 - c) * sales(thesaurus_nvm, q_opt(thesaurus_nvm))
- c * 0.2 / 12 * leftover(thesaurus_nvm, q_opt(thesaurus_nvm))
- 0.05 * lost_sales(thesaurus_nvm, q_opt(thesaurus_nvm)) 
)</code></pre>
<pre id='var-myp' class='code-output documenter-example-output'>357.91095265057226</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>(
 (2.75 - c) * sales(thesaurus_nvm, q_opt(thesaurus_nvm))
- c * 0.2 / 12 * leftover(thesaurus_nvm, q_opt(thesaurus_nvm))
- b * lost_sales(thesaurus_nvm, q_opt(thesaurus_nvm)) 
)</code></pre>
<pre id='var-hash168612' class='code-output documenter-example-output'>358.7751322584922</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>- - (2.75 - c) * lost_sales(thesaurus_nvm, q_opt(thesaurus_nvm))</code></pre>
<pre id='var-hash132077' class='code-output documenter-example-output'>1.115070461832147</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>(
underage_cost(thesaurus_nvm) *  sales(thesaurus_nvm, q_opt(thesaurus_nvm))
- overage_cost(thesaurus_nvm) *  leftover(thesaurus_nvm, q_opt(thesaurus_nvm))
+ profit_shift(thesaurus_nvm)
)</code></pre>
<pre id='var-hash694196' class='code-output documenter-example-output'>358.7751322584922</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>profit(thesaurus_nvm)</code></pre>
<pre id='var-hash695305' class='code-output documenter-example-output'>358.7751322584922</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>lost_sales(thesaurus_nvm, q_opt(thesaurus_nvm))</code></pre>
<pre id='var-hash146483' class='code-output documenter-example-output'>0.5575352309160735</pre>

<pre class='language-julia'><code class='language-julia'>solve(thesaurus_nvm)</code></pre>
<pre id='var-hash288191' class='code-output documenter-example-output'>=====================================
Results of maximizing expected profit

 * Expected profit: 358.78
=====================================
This is a consequence of
```
